BidiChecker is an open-source tool for the automated testing of web pages
for errors in support of bidirectional languages (those written from right
to left).

The user's guide, with instructions on installation and use, can be found
in the docs/ subdirectory of this package.

The subdirectories in this package:
docs/        The user's guide and the API documentation (in docs/jsdoc/).
lib/         Precompiled JavaScript for easy use in web page tests.
samples/     A sample application which demonstrates the use of BidiChecker.
src/         The JavaScript source code and unit tests, if you want to modify
             BidiChecker or understand its internals. Requires Closure Library.

For more information about BidiChecker, visit:
http://code.google.com/p/bidichecker
